{"id": 7019, "title": "Ticket #7019: Implement docker universe container cleanup backstop", "description": "<blockquote>\nNow that we label all htcondor created containers, we can have the startd remove all exitted containers when the startd starts.  This parallels the way the startd removes old execute directories.  In both cases, the starter usually does the cleanup, but having the startd also do it implements a backstop in case of crashes, reboots, etc.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2019-May-20 15:35:42 by tim:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>CODE REVIEW:</strong> Why defined a string for the label and then use a string constant and add comment that it must match? Should only have 1 string.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2019-May-21 09:18</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/d2e63cdb7694fba7689e706c08939aad804d2826\">[56911]</a></span>: Document <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=7019\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7019'); return false;\" title=\"Implement docker universe container cleanup backstop\">#7019</a></span>  (By Greg Thain )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2019-May-17 13:20</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/28f0920aed8549a7f3083486f791f38c43e4491f\">[56904]</a></span>: Prune any old htcondor containers on startd start <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?tick